@startuml Save and Load Report Flow
title Demo App Flow: Save & Load Report

actor "End-User" as User
participant "Demo App UI\n(AlpineJS)" as UI
participant "ReportBuilderController" as Controller
participant "ReportBuilderRequest\n(Factory)" as Factory
database "Database" as DB

== Saving a Report ==
User -> UI : Click "Save Configuration"
activate UI
UI -> UI : Serialize active AST
UI -> Controller : POST /save (name, description, AST JSON)
activate Controller

Controller -> Factory : ReportBuilderRequest::createFromPayload(JSON)
activate Factory
Factory --> Controller : Validated AST Request
deactivate Factory

Controller -> DB : Insert SavedReport (AST Serialized)
activate DB
activate DB
DB --> Controller : Success
deactivate DB
Controller --> UI : Response
deactivate Controller
UI --> User : Show "Saved!" Alert
deactivate UI

== Loading a Report ==
User -> UI : Open "Saved Reports Library"
activate UI
UI -> Controller : GET /saved
activate Controller
Controller -> DB : Select all SavedReports
activate DB
DB --> Controller : Array of Reports
deactivate DB
Controller --> UI : JSON List
deactivate Controller
UI --> User : Display Library Modal

User -> UI : Click "Load to Editor"
UI -> UI : fetch /saved/{id}
UI -> UI : Parse JSON Payload into AlpineJS State
note right: Recursively reconstructs UI panels\nfrom the strict AST
UI --> User : Editor visually populated
deactivate UI

@enduml
